Brand story:
IBM Innovator Begins Second Century of Its Existence
If someone were looking for a word that would most accurately express IBM's strategy, the closest would probably be "long-termism."
For the general public, IBM is a symbol of the technological revolution, it is a very contemporary company, and yet a hundred years have passed since its inception.
The foundation of this long-termism was laid by the first boss of the company, the visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He has already conceded the motto that a number of world problems can be easily solved if people are willing to think.
His motto "Think!" became an imprint, around which the life of the future giant (and also the name of an internal magazine, which began to be published at IBM in 1935).
It was also the basis of Watson's carefully constructed corporate culture.
“For us at IBM, long-term thinking means a continuous movement towards the future.
