In Michoacan, they analyze the possibility of counting "voice-by-vote"
According to data published by PREP, the difference between the first and second place in the governor's election is less than 27 percent. So far, the votes of 879 out of 6074 electoral districts have not been counted.
The possibility of counting "voice after the vote" appeared in this year's election in Michoacan, where in line with the data published by the Preliminary Election Results (PREP) program, the difference is between the first and second place in the governor's elections less than 27 percent, and it has not yet been counted on the votes of 879 out of a total of 6074 constituencies.
In this context, the President of the General Council of the Electoral Institute in Michoacán (IEM), María de los Ángeles Llanderal Zaragoza, recalled that a few days ago, on November 9, the electoral body approved a number of measures that should harmonize local standards with federal electoral reform.
As it will be recalled, Michoacán officially did not confirm his political constitution or his State Electoral Code or the Electoral Justice Act. The State Congress approved the reforms shortly before the statutory period of entry was due to expire, and Governor Leonel Godoy Rangel omitted their publication within the deadline in the Act of the Official State Gazette, stating that he had any objections to them.
On November 9, the Supreme State Court (SCJN) resolved the constitutional dispute initiated by local legislative power and declared the voice of the head of state on constitutional reforms "invalid and illegal" because it does not have the right to "not even approve or veto them".
When asked by the possibility of counting "voice by voice" María de los Ángeles Llanderal replied that, by approving the relevant measures, it would be possible for the partial and overall counts to be carried out by the local electoral body.
In this way, the partial counting of votes, one or more electoral parcels, may be made under the following conditions: the election results do not match; there is no entry of votes and the calculation in the relevant box or the President does not have it available; or if there have been errors and obvious violations of the election results.
Moreover, the total recount of votes in all ballot boxes will be possible if there is an indication that the difference between the potential winner of the election and the candidate in second place is less or equal to one percentage point; whenever an explicit request of a representative of the party and/or the coalition that proposed the candidate in second place at the beginning of the session appears.
The overall recount of the votes will also be possible when, after a proper account, it is established that the difference between the likely winner and the candidate in second place is equal to or less than one percentage point, and also whenever there is an explicit request from a political party whose candidate finished in second place. In this case, electoral parcels will be discarded, for which a partial count was made.
It should be mentioned that in such a situation there are elections in Morelia, where according to PREP, the difference between the first and second place is less than 0.16%, although 129 of the total 923 electoral districts have not yet been sumed.
