There was an eviction of the occupied house, in which gigantic parties were held
Aliens have appropriated 11 of 13 apartments in a building in Balmes, 51
12 occupiers left the house yesterday at noon, without resisting
All indications are that the nightmare experienced by neighbors from the number 51 in Balmes Street is finally over.
Twelve people volunteered yesterday at noon to the building they were inhabited illegally and where they organized gigantic parties that woke up neighbors. They left the building by order of the court and without having to intervene the police.
After the operation, the lock on the door was replaced to prevent the recurrence of the situation.
"Since now, the entrance will be guarded," the administrator said.
The occupiers, who took 11 of the 13 apartments in the building - the rest are inhabited - took away all the electrical and partially water equipment, in addition, they painted the walls and left behind the garbage all kinds, especially cans of alcoholic beverages.
In the first three apartments, huge parties were held, which lasted up to two days and woke up to other tenants.
Next to the building is a discotheque, Balmes 51, which was also damaged.
Its owner, Maria Pantinat, explained to Europa Press that as long as the building was occupied, sales fell by 80%.
The owner of the disco emphasizes that the occupiers of the building made her unfair competition, because they sold drinks for 3 euros, while at the discotheque it costs 10.
In addition, the entertainment business owner had to respond to neighbors' lawsuits due to noise. However, the problems were caused by the visitors of the discotheque, but by the inhabitants of the occupied house and especially those who participated in the parties held here, the frequency and intensity of which have increased in recent weeks, according to the agitated inhabitants of the surrounding area.
The owner of the discotheque explained that the problems were so big that they even agreed with the owner of the building and had been waiving her rent for nine months.
City police also confirmed that they have received more complaints from neighbors over the past few weeks about the situation.
The chairman of the city group of the People's Party of the PP at the town hall, Alberto Fernández Díaz, last week demanded that "the building be immediately evicted and thus put an end to the problems of civil coexistence that the neighbors suffer from, and the destruction of the area."
The chairman of the People's Party explained that only one floor was occupied before the summer, but in recent months the occupiers have reached all floors of the building and almost all the apartments, and in one of them there were even thefts.
In this regard, he added that "there is necessary to put an end to impunity and to be consistent in terms of acts against civil responsibility that occurred in the building."
Yesterday, city police also cleared the building in Nou Barris.
At 15 o'cate 30 minutes, police got into building 35 on Mont-ral Street after it was summoned by neighbors who saw four people entering the building.
All four were immediately detained.
Park or mountains?
Architects gathered on the occasion of the proceedings, which entails more than a controversy regarding fees
The 16-gate town selection process once again opens up a debate about the role of Collserola Park in Barcelona.
In the mid 80's, at the time of the greatest heyday of the already defunct Corporación Metropolitana de Barcelona (CMB), this self-government printed several pamphlets in support of Collserola Park.
The flyer defined the mountain as a large park of the metropolitan Barcelona.
What's more, it was supplemented by a numerical comparison with New York's Central Park.
After the CMB ceased to exist in 1987, the park returned to the mind of many as the upper frontier of Barcelona. The Catalan metropolis is one of the few that is not oriented on the north-south axis, but up (mountains) - down (sea).
Collserola qualifying as a natural park is going in this direction.
The reference was no longer Central Park, but Yellowstone with wild boars instead of the Yogi bear.
Such was the position until September, when the town hall announced a mega competition consisting of 16 auditions on the same number of entrance gates to Collserola.
The gate, of course, plays rather the idea of the park.
Either this, or someone is trying to place the gate in the field.
So there is only one question: Collserola, a park or a mountain?
During the competition, both in terms of purely organizational and on the basis of reflection on the city, this question becomes the central theme of all Barcelona architects.
It is already as bitter theme as when two members of this old caste of the chosen ones shake hands when meeting in an elevator.
And it was this feat that provoked one of the rare matches between three Barcelona architects and the pre-ached university professors think.
Miguel Roldán, Daniel Modol and Marta Bayona: the selection process has its justification.
According to Roldán, after the question of the Bay party began, "it is necessary" to discuss the "mountain party", so the speech of Ildefons Cerd about the green apples was not finished.
"We have to follow the principle that the largest Barcelona park is the beach.
Among other things, its great accessibility.
Collserola is more complex," said the architect, for whom the name "gateway to Collserola" carries "lexilogical trap": we must not imagine them "as entrances to the park, but rather as a delimitation of zones where it is possible to act".
The idol, like Roldán and Bayona, with the experience of the world of urbanism, qualifies the proposal as a "intellectual challenge" offering "one of the dangers."
The danger resulting from "uncertainty, which today represents the project of a public place" after the experience of the 80's, which had "her swan singing" in the Forum area.
The first concern is the very demarcatement of the boundaries where it should be built.
“To define something is to take the next step,” that is, in principle, move one step further.
"It is necessary to keep in mind the new urban and planning tools, because the current ones (with reference to the General Metropolitan Plan (PGM)) can cause a real disaster."
If we focus in more detail on the question, Mododol believes that the Collserola valley slope can be "deemed as a park", but the Barcelona part is not, for purely topographic reasons.
Mododol also recalled that there was already a work carried out by Patronat de Collserola, which "cannot end up in the rubbuff," even though he welcomes the fact that the town hall offers his gremia to intervene in the project from "first time".
Moreover, he understands that the proximity of the mountain and the city is a kind of pass that allows architects to engage in the debate, but he "doubles" that this should be this technical profile that will lead multidisciplinary teams ("it's all about skill," he adds), which needs to be created: "Architects should only be tools."
Bayona suggests that the answer to the question that gave the title to this game is complex, because in the basis for the selection process lacks a global vision Collserola: "16 tenders have been announced that deal with all the axis of the mountain - the sea, but there is no longitudinal study to look at the area and understand it as a whole."
This makes it possible that at least he has applied for all 16 tenders.
Otherwise, the project of one gate can allude to the concept and definition of the architect of the neighboring gate.
In his view, the town hall should guarantee that the zone located immediately above Ronda de Dalt should secure a zone of equipment in its entire length, which would ensure a smooth transition between the city and the greenery.
