Clearly speaking, without the consent of the company, an employee who falls ill would lose four days of wages, i.e. at least 15% of his monthly income.
A measure that risks causing a lot of bad blood, but which, according to Les Echos, could bring 280 million euros.
And also a measure that would be accompanied by another measure of symbolic reach: to give civil servants one day unpaid incapacity for work (when they have no incapacity for three days in the private sector so far).
