But it is known from Napoleon that it was an easy idea.
Universal suffrage, although a necessary condition for democracy, is not a prerequisite, and it can become a “instrument tool” as the Republican philosopher Etienne Vacherot once said.
No, democracy requires much more: public space, public spirit, values, organization of separation and control of power, education, enlightenment, social and economic solidarity, justice.
The crisis of Europe we are experiencing is an economic crisis, but it is just as it has been and since the beginning of the crisis of politics and democracy.
